==English==

===Etymology===
1792, from {{etyl|fr|en}} {{m|fr|acclimater}}, from {{m|fr|à}} + {{m|fr|climat||climate}} from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|ad}} + {{m|la|climat}}, (English {{m|en|climate}}) from {{etyl|grc|en}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} – see {{m|en|climate}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ə.ˈklaɪ.mət/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈæk.lɪ.meɪt/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|en-us-acclimate.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|acclimat}}

# {{lb|en|transitive|chiefly|US}} To [[habituate]] to a [[climate]] not native; to [[acclimatize]].
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[adjust]] to a new [[environment]]; not necessarily a wild, natural, earthy one.
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To become accustomed to a new climate or environment.

